Date:  0/10/2000
Source:  NZWords
Author:
Vol / Page:  4 : 2
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Maoriland</i> is the earliest of these [informal nicknames], recorded in <i>AND</i> from 1859 and <i>DNZE</i> from 1865; this was a common journalistic term in Australia in the 1880s and later (popularised in particular by the Sydney <i>Bulletin</i>, but it has long since had its day.
