Edition:
Quote:  <i>Maoriland, n</i>. a modern name for New Zealand. It is hardly earlier than 1884. If the word, or anything like it, such as <i>Maoria</i>, was used earlier, it meant `the Maori parts of New Zealand.' It is now used for the whole.
